The paper discusses the implementation of a practical verifier for data-driven workflows, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of model checking, which is a technique commonly used in programming languages and compilers (cs.PL). The paper discusses the verification of temporal properties, which is a topic in logic and formal methods (cs.LO). The paper also mentions the complexity of the verification process, which is a topic in cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of off-the-shelf verifiers, which is a topic in distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
